[Crim. No. 738. Second Appellate District, Division Two. August 10, 1920.] In the Matter of the Application of JAMES E. TIFFANY for a Writ of Habeas Corpus in Behalf of MILO JAMES TIFFANY.

*796W. W. Judd for Petitioner.

Paul W. Schenck and Richard Kittrelle for Respondent.

THE COURT.

The facts in this proceeding are in all material respects the same as in Matter of William McFarland Tiffany, ante, p. 44, [192 Pac. 547]. For reasons there given, the writ is discharged.
